cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.SD 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with machine translation between Hindi and English for medical communication. It also involves the use of various methods for data gathering and augmentation, which are common techniques in natural language processing research. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the development of a machine translation system. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it addresses the issue of language barriers faced by migrant workers in Qatar and the potential impact on their access to healthcare. 

Finally, it could be classified under cs.SD (Sound) as it mentions the low-resource nature of the language pair, especially for speech, which could involve research on speech recognition and synthesis.
